topLevelComment.text: Hey great videos man, gonna sub! Question: Audio, can‚Äôt see any comments on this. I‚Äôm assuming the MK5 acts only as an audio source and not amplification? My 350z BOSE audio was instantly ripped out but with the BOSE premium in my Q60 the audio is like pretty decent. So I‚Äôm conscious to avoid downgrading audio just for the screen. Cheers
topLevelComment.author: @dirtydogbox

replies.text: Thx for the support Wasso!!! So consider the MK5 a source that you'd plug into your aux port, like a phone or mp3 player. That's exactly how it behaves, it piggybacks the AUX. If you have Bose, all the amplifying and sound processing will still be handled downstream.  The MK5 has its own EQ but I leave flat and just let the Bose do it's thing.  Hope that helps!!
